  "text": "The source data for risk assessment are given below in Tables 1 and 2 [CITATION_1] . Mentioned in Tables 1 and 2 data represent standardized values of the actual value (in accordance with paragraph three of methodical). The standardized statistical data are grouped into three possible states specified in the methodology: minimum, maximum permissible, and unacceptably high level of risk effect on the project respectively. The principle of direct relationship between the increasing risk level (from the first group to the third group) and the increase in the risk indicator value underlies the grouping of risks.",
